The patient developed generalized skin peeling starting about one month after initiating antiepileptic drugs, which suggests an adverse reaction possibly related to medications like phenytoin. Given the rapid onset and extensive involvement along with the timeline post-medication start, toxic epidermal necrolysis (TEN), a severe drug reaction, becomes highly likely among the given choices.
\boxed{D}
(Note: While fixed drug eruption could theoretically occur post-initiation of new meds, its typical pattern does not align well with "generalized" and excluding hands/feet findings; similarly, while pemphigus might present similarly, there isn't strong enough evidence here pointing towards chronic immune-mediated processes rather than acute drug reaction.)

